-- Portugal Hotel Revenue Rises 1.6 Percent in February, INE Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2013-04-16T10:04:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-16/portugal-hotel-revenue-rises-1-6-percent-in-february-ine-says.html
Portugal ’s hotels recorded a 1.6
percent rise in revenue in February from the same month last
year as overnight stays by Irish, British, German and Dutch
tourists increased.  Revenue rose to 82.3 million euros ($107.6 million) in
February, the Lisbon-based National Statistics Institute said
today in an e-mailed statement. In the first two months of the
year, revenue was unchanged at 155.4 million euros.  Tourism represents about a tenth of Portugal’s gross
domestic product, according to the  Economy Ministry .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
